Animals are multicellular eukaryotic organisms that forms the biological kingdom Animalia.
With few exceptions, animals consume organic material, breathe oxygen, are able to move and grow from a hollow sphere of cells, the blastula, during embryonic development.
Animals have complex interactions with each other and their environments, forming intricate food webs.
The study of animals is called zoology.
